<quiz>
  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Quadratic equation from stacking classroom chairs</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>
During a school event, chairs are arranged in rows in the hall. There are \(x\) rows of chairs, and each row has \( (x + {@k@}) \) chairs. Altogether, {@T@} chairs were arranged.
</p>

<p>(a) Form a quadratic equation representing the situation.</p>
<p>[[input:eqn1]] [[validation:eqn1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>

<p>(b) Determine the value of \(x\).</p>
<p>\(x =\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt2]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
Let the number of chairs in the first row be \(x\).
</p>

<p>
The next row has \(x + {@k@}\) chairs.
</p>

<p>
To find the total number of chairs arranged, we multiply the number of rows by the number of chairs in the next row. This gives the total number of chairs arranged in the hall.
</p>

<p>
Therefore,
</p>

<p>
\[
x(x + {@k@}) = {@T@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Expand the expression.
</p>

<p>
\[
x^2 + {@k@}x = {@T@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Rearrange the equation into standard quadratic form.
</p>

<p>
\[
x^2 + {@k@}x - {@T@} = 0
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Factorise the quadratic expression.
</p>

<p>
\[
(x - {@r@})(x + {@r + k@}) = 0
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 4: Solve the equation.
</p>

<p>
\[
x = {@r@} \quad \text{or} \quad x = -{@r + k@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Since the number of chairs cannot be negative,
</p>

<p>
\[
x = {@r@}
\]
</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
